claim.claim-text:
A self-propelled robot (1) for the treatment of a surface, comprising:
- a protective guard (2);
- at least one tool (3);
- movement means (4) comprising at least two motor-driven wheels (4a) to allow the movement of the self-propelled robot (1) on a travel path;
- at least one mechanical power transmission (5) designed to actuate the self-propelled robot (1), and wherein the at least one mechanical power transmission (5) comprises at least one motor element (3c, 4c) and at least one driven element (3b, 4a) which are operatively associated by a magnetic field, the mechanical power transmission (5) being operatively associated with the at least two motor-driven wheels (4a) of the movement means (4), characterised in that the motor element (3c, 4c) of the mechanical power transmission (5) comprises an electric motor (3c, 4c) having an energising drum (7) keyed on its own shaft (6), the energising drum (7) being preferably rotatable about an axis of rotation ("X"), and wherein the driven element (3b, 4a) of the mechanical power transmission (5) comprises at least one driven crown (8) having a plurality of plates (8a made of ferromagnetic material, the driven element (3b, 4a) of the mechanical power transmission also comprises respective hubs (4d) of the at least two motor-driven wheels (4a).
